# MCP + admin HTTP examples (VS Code REST Client, IntelliJ HTTP Client, etc.)
# Set @base to your server URL (default MCP REST port from app settings).
#
# --- Quick test plan ---
# 1. GET  {{base}}/health  → 200, { "status": "ok", ... }
# 2. POST {{base}}/mcp     → initialize (below) → result with protocolVersion, serverInfo, instructions
# 3. POST {{base}}/mcp     → notifications/initialized → 204 No Content
# 4. POST {{base}}/mcp     → tools/list → result.tools includes search_corpus, web_search, …
# 5. POST {{base}}/mcp     → tools/call search_corpus (below) → result.content[0].text JSON
# 6. POST {{base}}/mcp     → tools/call list_namespaces → namespaces + activeNamespace
# 7. POST {{base}}/mcp     → tools/call web_search (below) → needs Google CSE in app settings
# Admin REST (not MCP): same paths under /admin and /store. Optional query: ?namespace=<corpusName>

@base = http://localhost:3000

### Health
GET {{base}}/health

### MCP metadata (GET)
GET {{base}}/mcp

### JSON-RPC: initialize
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "http-test", "version": "1.0.0" }
  },
  "id": 1
}

### JSON-RPC: notifications/initialized (no response body — expect 204)
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "notifications/initialized",
  "params": {}
}

### JSON-RPC: tools/list
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/list",
  "params": {},
  "id": 2
}

### JSON-RPC: tools/call — search_corpus
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "search_corpus",
    "arguments": {
      "query": "example",
      "topK": 5,
      "filters": { "algorithm": "hybrid" }
    }
  },
  "id": 3
}

### JSON-RPC: tools/call — search_corpus (scoped to one namespace)
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "search_corpus",
    "arguments": {
      "query": "example",
      "topK": 5,
      "namespace": "general",
      "filters": { "algorithm": "hybrid" }
    }
  },
  "id": 3b
}

### JSON-RPC: tools/call — list_namespaces
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": { "name": "list_namespaces", "arguments": {} },
  "id": 3n
}

### JSON-RPC: tools/call — web_search (requires Google CSE configured in app)
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "web_search",
    "arguments": { "query": "Model Context Protocol", "maxResults": 3 }
  },
  "id": 4
}

### JSON-RPC: resources/list (optional; not advertised in initialize.capabilities)
POST {{base}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "resources/list",
  "params": {},
  "id": 5
}

### Admin: list documents
GET {{base}}/admin/documents

### Admin: list documents in one namespace
GET {{base}}/admin/documents?namespace=general

### Store alias: same as /admin/documents
GET {{base}}/store/documents

### Admin: corpus-only search (REST helper, not MCP)
POST {{base}}/admin/corpus-search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "example",
  "limit": 5,
  "algorithm": "hybrid",
  "webSearch": false,
  "namespace": "general"
}
